{
  "texts": [
    "For this case, we selected one or two tweets from the authority timeline posted soon before the rumor time, and assigned the other label to those pairs.",
    "In reality, most of the tweets in authority timelines are neither supporting nor denying a given rumor.",
    "To get closer to that real scenario, for each agree and disagree pair, we manually examined the timeline of the authority within the same time period of the rumor, and selected at most two tweets, where we give higher priority to tweets related to the rumor's topic or at least have an overlap in some keywords with the rumor.",
    "A tweet of those is then labeled as other if it is either relevant to the rumor but is neither disagreeing nor agreeing with it, or it is completely irrelevant to it.",
    "We ended up with 466 other pairs."
  ]
}